This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   - Fix a bug where `autoPaths: true` with empty `customPaths` doesn't work for series URLs
   - Fix Chinese (Unicode) post URLs broken under autoPaths/customPaths routes
   - Fix test failures caused by `site.config.ts` having `autoPaths: true` and a renamed test fixture file
   - Fix integration test failures caused by the same renamed fixture
   - Address CodeRabbit PR #46 review comments:
     - Round 1: align `reservedSlugs` hardcoded list with `RESERVED_ROUTE_SEGMENTS` constant
     - Round 2: replace `in` operator with `Object.hasOwn()` for prototype-safe checks, and add missing test coverage for autoPaths routing scenarios

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Next.js 15+ App Router with `output: "export"` (static export), `dynamicParams = false`
   - `generateStaticParams()` must return non-empty params for all dynamic routes
   - ESM live bindings and how `mock.module()` in bun:test updates them
   - `autoPaths` feature: when enabled, series posts served at `/{series-slug}/{post-slug}` instead of `/posts/{slug}`
   - `customPaths` feature: per-series custom URL prefix overriding `autoPaths`
   - Percent-encoding workaround for Unicode slugs in Next.js dev mode under `output: "export"` (dev server sends encoded URLs, but `generateStaticParams` provides raw Unicode)
   - `in` operator vs `Object.hasOwn()` for own-property checks (prototype chain safety)
   - bun:test module mocking: `mock.module()` replaces in place, but live binding updates may not reliably propagate to previously-cached modules in certain conditions
   - Test isolation: `beforeAll`/`afterAll` vs `beforeEach`/`afterEach` for mock state management

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`src/lib/urls.ts`**
     - Changed `RESERVED_ROUTE_SEGMENTS` from `const` to `export const`, added `'posts'` and `'search'`
     - Changed `if (slug in customPaths)` → `if (Object.hasOwn(customPaths, slug))`
     ```typescript
     export const RESERVED_ROUTE_SEGMENTS = new Set([
       'posts', 'series', 'books', 'flows', 'tags', 'authors', 'archive', 'notes', 'graph', 'search', 'page', 'api',
     ]);
     // in validateSeriesAutoPaths:
     if (Object.hasOwn(customPaths, slug)) continue; // Has an explicit override — skip
     ```

   - **`src/app/[slug]/page.tsx`**
     - Added `getAllSeries`, `getSeriesAutoPaths`, `RESERVED_ROUTE_SEGMENTS` to imports
     - `generateStaticParams`: added autoPaths series slug generation, replaced hardcoded reserved list with `...RESERVED_ROUTE_SEGMENTS`
     - `generateMetadata` and `Page`: extended `matchedSeriesSlug` to also detect autoPaths series
     - Changed `in customPaths` → `Object.hasOwn(customPaths, ...)` in 3 places
     ```typescript
     const matchedSeriesSlug =
       Object.entries(customPaths).find(([, path]) => path === slug)?.[0] ??
       (getSeriesAutoPaths() && !Object.hasOwn(customPaths, slug) && getSeriesData(slug) ? slug : undefined);
     // generateStaticParams reservedSlugs:
     const reservedSlugs = new Set([
       ...pages.map(p => p.slug),
       basePath,
       ...Object.values(customPaths),
       ...autoPathSlugs,
       ...RESERVED_ROUTE_SEGMENTS,
     ]);
     ```

   - **`src/app/[slug]/[postSlug]/page.tsx`**
     - Added Unicode encoding workaround for `generateStaticParams` (mirrors `posts/[slug]/page.tsx`)
     - Changed `in customPaths` → `Object.hasOwn(customPaths, ...)` in 2 places
     ```typescript
     // Work around Next dev static-param checks for percent-encoded Unicode postSlugs
     if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {
       const existing = new Set(params.map(p => `${p.slug}/${p.postSlug}`));
       for (const p of [...params]) {
         const encodedPostSlug = encodeURIComponent(p.postSlug);
         const key = `${p.slug}/${encodedPostSlug}`;
         if (!existing.has(key)) {
           existing.add(key);
           params.push({ slug: p.slug, postSlug: encodedPostSlug });
         }
       }
     }
     // Also:
     if (Object.hasOwn(customPaths, seriesSlug)) continue;
     const isAutoSeriesPath = getSeriesAutoPaths() && !Object.hasOwn(customPaths, prefix) && getSeriesData(prefix) !== null;
     ```

   - **`src/app/[slug]/page/[page]/page.tsx`**
     - Added `getAllSeries`, `getSeriesAutoPaths` to imports
     - `generateStaticParams`: added autoPaths paginated series params
     - `generateMetadata` and `PrefixPageRoute`: extended `matchedSeriesSlug` to detect autoPaths series
     - Changed `in customPaths` → `Object.hasOwn(customPaths, ...)` in 3 places
     ```typescript
     const matchedSeriesSlug =
       Object.entries(customPaths).find(([, path]) => path === prefix)?.[0] ??
       (getSeriesAutoPaths() && !Object.hasOwn(customPaths, prefix) && getSeriesData(prefix) ? prefix : undefined);
     if (Object.hasOwn(customPaths, seriesSlug)) continue;
     ```

   - **`site.config.ts`**
     - Reverted `autoPaths: true` → `autoPaths: false` (was accidentally set to true as test scaffolding)

   - **`tests/integration/markdown-features.test.ts`**
     - Updated `getPostBySlug("multilingual-test")` → `getPostBySlug("multilingual-test-中文长标题")` (3 occurrences) after the test fixture file was renamed

   - **`tests/integration/reading-time-headings.test.ts`**
     - Updated `getPostBySlug("multilingual-test")` → `getPostBySlug("multilingual-test-中文长标题")`

   - **`tests/unit/static-params.test.ts`** (IN PROGRESS)
     - Added `import * as realUrls from '../../src/lib/urls'`
     - Updated outer `afterAll` to also restore `@/lib/urls`
     - Added new tests in `autoPaths series routing`:
       - `[slug]/page throws when redirectFrom conflicts with 'posts'`
       - `[slug]/page includes Unicode single-segment redirectFrom slug`
     - Added `describe('autoPaths enabled')` with `beforeEach`/`afterEach` (using `mock.module('@/lib/urls', ...)`) containing:
       - `[slug]/page includes auto-path series slug when autoPaths enabled`
       - `[slug]/page includes Unicode auto-path series slug when autoPaths enabled`
       - `[slug]/page uses customPaths prefix for series with override, not the series slug`
     - Added Unicode encoding tests in `custom path routes` (currently being rewritten to use `redirectFrom` approach instead of url mocking)

   - **`tests/unit/urls.test.ts`**
     - No changes made; failing tests here were caused by mock leakage from `static-params.test.ts`

4. Errors and fixes:
   - **`autoPaths` not working in series listing routes**: `[slug]/page.tsx` and `[slug]/page/[page]/page.tsx` only handled `customPaths` not `autoPaths`. Fixed by adding `getSeriesAutoPaths()` checks and `getAllSeries()` calls in all three sections of each file (`generateStaticParams`, `generateMetadata`, route component).
   - **Chinese URLs broken in autoPaths/customPaths routes**: `[slug]/[postSlug]/page.tsx` lacked the `encodeURIComponent` dev-mode workaround present in `posts/[slug]/page.tsx`. Fixed by adding the same workaround.
   - **Unit test failures after committing**: `site.config.ts` had `autoPaths: true` (committed as test scaffolding), breaking tests expecting `autoPaths: false`. Fixed by reverting to `false`.
   - **Integration test failures**: Two test files referenced old slug `multilingual-test` after the file was renamed to `multilingual-test-中文长标题.mdx`. Fixed by updating slug references in both files.
   - **Mock state leaking between tests**: In `autoPaths enabled` describe, using `beforeAll` instead of `beforeEach` caused test 3 (which inline-overrides the mock with `customPaths: {'my-series': 'articles'}`) to pollute tests 4 & 5. Also, the `custom path routes` inline mock calls leaked into `urls.test.ts`. Fix: switched `autoPaths enabled` to use `beforeEach`/`afterEach`, removed `[slug]/[postSlug]` autoPaths tests that required unreliable cross-module live-binding updates, rewrote Unicode encoding tests to use `redirectFrom` instead of `@/lib/urls` mock.
   - **`mock.module` live binding not updating `[slug]/[postSlug]/page.tsx`**: Mocking `@/lib/urls` via `beforeAll` updated live bindings in `[slug]/page.tsx` but NOT in `[slug]/[postSlug]/page.tsx` (reason unclear - likely bun module cache behavior). Dropped those tests rather than fighting the framework.

5. Problem Solving:
   - Identified that the `autoPaths` bug affected 2 listing route files (`[slug]/page.tsx`, `[slug]/page/[page]/page.tsx`) but NOT the post route (`[slug]/[postSlug]/page.tsx` which already handled it)
   - Identified that the Unicode workaround from `posts/[slug]/page.tsx` needed to be replicated in `[slug]/[postSlug]/page.tsx`
   - Identified that `Object.hasOwn()` is the correct ES2022 replacement for prototype-safe own-property checks vs the `in` operator
   - Identified that bun's `mock.module()` may not reliably update live bindings in previously-cached modules loaded through dynamic imports — discovered empirically when `[slug]/page.tsx` mock worked but `[slug]/[postSlug]/page.tsx` did not
   - Ongoing: rewriting Unicode encoding tests in `custom path routes` to use `redirectFrom` with Unicode postSlug (no `@/lib/urls` mock needed)

6. All user messages:
   - "There is a bug in the series URL: if 'customPaths' is empty, the 'autoPaths: true' configuration doesn't seem to work."
   - "If 'autoPaths' is set to true and we use the series path, the Chinese URL of the post breaks. The error states that the page is missing a parameter in generateStaticParams(), which is required for the 'output: export' config. Notably, Chinese URLs for posts in the /posts path work fine."
   - "OK, I just misunderstood." (after asking "what is your opinion?" about something unrelated)
   - `/commit` (skill invocation)
   - `bun test test failed: [test output showing autoPaths unit test failures]`
   - `/commit` (skill invocation)
   - `test:int failed: [integration test failures for multilingual-test slug]`
   - `/commit` (skill invocation)
   - "check about code reviews by coderabbit, PR #46"
   - "OK, fix it." (to apply the CodeRabbit reservedSlugs refactor)
   - `/commit` (skill invocation)
   - "check about the new code review comments by coderabbit, PR #46"
   - "what is your opinion?" (about whether to fix test coverage)
   - "if test coverage is valuable, why not fix?" (pushing back on assistant's recommendation to skip tests)

7. Pending Tasks:
   - Complete the rewrite of Unicode encoding tests in `custom path routes` of `static-params.test.ts` to use `redirectFrom` approach (no `@/lib/urls` mock)
   - Run `bun run test:unit` to verify all tests pass after the fixes
   - Commit the complete set of changes (`Object.hasOwn` fixes + new tests)

8. Current Work:
   The assistant was in the middle of fixing 6 failing unit tests in `tests/unit/static-params.test.ts` after adding new tests for CodeRabbit's review feedback. The last edit rewrote the `autoPaths enabled` describe block:

   ```typescript
   describe('autoPaths enabled', () => {
     // Use beforeEach (not beforeAll) so each test starts with a clean base mock
     beforeEach(() => {
       mock.module('@/lib/urls', () => ({
         ...realUrls,
         getSeriesAutoPaths: () => true,
         getSeriesCustomPaths: () => ({}),
         getPostUrl: (post: { slug: string; series?: string }) =>
           post.series ? `/${post.series}/${post.slug}` : `/posts/${post.slug}`,
         validateSeriesAutoPaths: () => {},
       }));
     });

     afterEach(() => {
       mock.module('@/lib/urls', () => realUrls);
