     test('[slug]/page includes auto-path series slug when autoPaths enabled', ...);
     test('[slug]/page includes Unicode auto-path series slug when autoPaths enabled', ...);
     test('[slug]/page uses customPaths prefix for series with override, not the series slug', ...);
     // [slug]/[postSlug] autoPaths tests were DROPPED (mock doesn't reliably update cached module)
   });
   ```

   Still remaining in `custom path routes`: two Unicode encoding tests that currently mock `@/lib/urls` inline (causing leak into `urls.test.ts`) and also fail because `getSeriesPosts` returns `[]`. These need to be rewritten to use `redirectFrom` with a Unicode postSlug instead.

9. Optional Next Step:
   The immediate next step is to rewrite the two failing Unicode encoding tests in `custom path routes` to use `redirectFrom` with a Unicode `postSlug` instead of mocking `@/lib/urls`. This removes the mock leak into `urls.test.ts` and makes the tests work within the existing mock infrastructure. The current broken tests are:

   ```
   custom path routes > [slug]/[postSlug] includes encoded Unicode postSlug variants in non-production
   custom path routes > [slug]/[postSlug] does not include encoded Unicode postSlug variants in production
   ```

   These should be rewritten as:
